  1. Oxford 3000
  2. Oxford 10

Words 901-1000

  1. entry
    She made her entry into the room with a big smile.

  2. environment
    We must protect the environment for future generations.

  3. environmental
    The company is working on reducing its environmental impact.

  4. episode
    I missed the latest episode of my favorite show.

  5. equal
    All people should have equal rights.

  6. equally
    The cake was divided equally among the children.

  7. equipment
    The gym has all the equipment you need for a good workout.

  8. error
    There was an error in the calculation.

  9. escape
    The prisoners planned their escape carefully.

  10. especially
    I love fruit, especially apples and bananas.

  11. essay
    She wrote an essay about her favorite book.

  12. essential
    Water is essential for life.

  13. establish
    The company was established in 1990.

  14. estate
    He inherited a large estate from his uncle.

  15. estimate
    Can you estimate how much this will cost?

  16. ethical
    It is important to make ethical decisions in business.

  17. euro
    The price of the book is ten euros.

  18. evaluate
    The teacher will evaluate your performance next week.

  19. even
    The road was not even, making it hard to walk.

  20. evening
    We went for a walk in the evening.

  21. event
    The concert was the biggest event of the year.

  22. eventually
    She eventually found her lost keys.

  23. ever
    Have you ever been to Paris?

  24. every
    Every student must complete the assignment.

  25. everybody
    Everybody was excited about the trip.

  26. everyday
    These shoes are perfect for everyday use.

  27. everyone
    Everyone enjoyed the party.

  28. everything
    Everything in the store is on sale.

  29. everywhere
    I looked everywhere for my phone.

  30. evidence
    The police found evidence at the crime scene.

  31. evil
    The story is about the battle between good and evil.

  32. exact
    Can you tell me the exact time of the meeting?

  33. exactly
    That is exactly what I was looking for.

  34. exam
    She studied hard for the math exam.

  35. examination
    The doctor performed a thorough examination.

  36. examine
    The scientist will examine the results carefully.

  37. example
    This is an example of a well-written essay.

  38. excellent
    She did an excellent job on the project.

  39. except
    Everyone except John attended the meeting.

  40. exchange
    They decided to exchange gifts during the holidays.

  41. excited
    The children were excited about the trip.

  42. excitement
    The excitement in the room was palpable.

  43. exciting
    The movie was so exciting that I watched it twice.

  44. excuse
    Please excuse me for being late.

  45. executive
    The executive made an important decision for the company.

  46. exercise
    Regular exercise is good for your health.

  47. exhibition
    The art exhibition attracted many visitors.

  48. exist
    Do you believe aliens exist?

  49. existence
    The existence of life on other planets is still a mystery.

  50. expand
    The company plans to expand its operations next year.

  51. expect
    I expect to finish the project by tomorrow.

  52. expectation
    The results exceeded our expectations.

  53. expected
    The train arrived earlier than expected.

  54. expedition
    They went on an expedition to explore the jungle.

  55. expense
    The trip was worth the expense.

  56. expensive
    This car is too expensive for me to buy.

  57. experience
    She has a lot of experience in teaching.

  58. experienced
    He is an experienced driver.

  59. experiment
    The scientist conducted an experiment in the lab.

  60. expert
    She is an expert in computer programming.

  61. explain
    Can you explain this concept to me?

  62. explanation
    His explanation was clear and easy to understand.

  63. explode
    The balloon will explode if you blow too much air into it.

  64. exploration
    Space exploration has always fascinated me.

  65. explore
    We decided to explore the city on foot.

  66. explosion
    The explosion was heard from miles away.

  67. export
    The country exports a lot of rice to other nations.

  68. expose
    The documentary aims to expose corruption in politics.

  69. express
    She found it hard to express her feelings.

  70. expression
    His facial expression showed that he was surprised.

  71. extend
    We decided to extend our stay by a few days.

  72. extent
    The extent of the damage was not clear.

  73. external
    The external walls of the house need painting.

  74. extra
    Can I have an extra slice of cake?

  75. extraordinary
    She has an extraordinary talent for music.

  76. extreme
    The weather conditions were extreme during the storm.

  77. extremely
    The movie was extremely interesting.

  78. eye
    She has beautiful blue eyes.

  79. face
    He had a big smile on his face.

  80. facility
    The hotel has excellent facilities for guests.

  81. fact
    It is a fact that the Earth orbits the Sun.

  82. factor
    Hard work is a key factor in success.

  83. factory
    The factory produces thousands of cars every year.

  84. fail
    He worked hard because he didn’t want to fail the test.

  85. failure
    Failure is often the first step to success.

  86. fair
    The teacher was fair in grading the exams.

  87. fairly
    The task was fairly easy to complete.

  88. faith
    She has great faith in her abilities.

  89. fall
    The leaves fall from the trees in autumn.

  90. false
    The statement he made was completely false.

  91. familiar
    This place looks familiar to me.

  92. family
    She spends a lot of time with her family.

  93. famous
    He is a famous actor known worldwide.

  94. fan
    She is a big fan of that band.

  95. fancy
    They went to a fancy restaurant for dinner.

  96. fantastic
    The view from the top of the mountain was fantastic.

  97. far
    The school is not far from my house.

  98. farm
    They live on a small farm in the countryside.

  99. farmer
    The farmer works hard to grow crops.

  100. farming
    Farming is an important part of the local economy.
